title: PPPP’s  Awais Qadir wins PS-23 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Syed Awais Qadir Shah has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-23, Sukkur – II by securing 69,266 votes.
According to unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Iayyat Ullah of Grand Democratic Alliance, who bagged votes 21137.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 52.15 %.
